OL,3,CMore time on social media 'linked to
OL,4,Csmoking and vape use among teenagers'
OL,6,FSpending a lot of time on social media
OL,7,Fcould increase the chances of
OL,8,Fteenagers taking up smoking or vaping,
OL,9,Faccording to a study.
OL,11,FThe findings advocate for the
OL,12,Fpromotion of healthy online habits for
OL,13,Fyoung people, researchers said, rather
OL,14,Fthan "blanket bans and over-
OL,15,Fprotection".
OL,17,FAcademics from the University of
OL,18,FGlasgow explored how social media use
OL,19,Famong 14-year-olds influenced nicotine
OL,20,Fuse when they reached 17.
