OL,3,CMore time on social media 'linked to
OL,4,Csmoking and vape use among teenagers'
OL,6,FResearchers found that spending more
OL,7,Fthan two hours a day on social media
OL,8,Fplatforms increased the likelihood of
OL,9,Fa teenager smoking by two and a half
OL,10,Ftimes.
OL,12,FThey were also more than three times
OL,13,Fmore likely to vape when compared to
OL,14,Ftheir peers who used social media for
OL,15,Fone hour to less than 30 minutes a day.
